{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id80bace02-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3502"},"text":"§ 3502.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Planned public works","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80bace03-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Advances To Ensure Planning","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding section 3324(a) and (b) of title 31, the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development may make advances to public agencies and Indian tribes—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80bace04-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to encourage public agencies and Indian tribes to maintain at all times a current and adequate reserve of planned public works the construction of which can rapidly be commenced, particularly when the national or local economic situation makes that action desirable; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80bace05-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to help attain maximum economy and efficiency in the planning and construction of public works.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80bace06-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Uses of Advances","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A public agency or Indian tribe shall use an advance under subsection (a) to aid in financing the cost of feasibility studies, engineering and architectural surveys, designs, plans, working drawings, specifications, or other action preliminary to and in preparation for the construction of public works, and for construction in connection with the development of a medical center, a general plan for the development of the center.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80bace07-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"No Future Commitment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"An advance under subsection (a) does not commit the Congress to appropriate amounts to assist in financing the construction of any public works planned with the aid of that advance. Outstanding advances to public agencies and Indian tribes in a State shall not exceed 12.5 percent of the aggregate then authorized to be appropriated to the revolving fund established under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s3503"},"text":"section 3503 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80bace08-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Requirements for Advances","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"An advance shall not be made under subsection (a) for an individual project (including a regional, metropolitan, or other areawide project) unless—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80bace09-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the project is planned to be constructed within or over a reasonable period of time considering the nature of the project;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80bace0a-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the project conforms to an overall state, local, or regional plan approved by a competent state, local, or regional authority; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80bace0b-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the public agency or Indian tribe formally contracts with the Federal Government to complete the plan preparation promptly and to repay part or all of the advance when due.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80bace0c-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3502/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Regulations","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may prescribe regulations to carry out this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id80bace0d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1167"},"text":"116 Stat. 1167","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id80bace0e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id80bace0f-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"id80bace10-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"3502","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"40:462(a), (b), (d).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-02/ch649"},"text":"Aug. 2, 1954, ch. 649","children":[],"tail":", title VII, § 702(a), (b), (d), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/641"},"text":"68 Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-11/ch783"},"text":"Aug. 11, 1955, ch. 783","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 112, "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/641"},"text":"69 Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/70/tV/s502/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–70, title V, § 502(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"June 30, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/175"},"text":"75 Stat. 175","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/560/tVI/s602/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–560, title VI, § 602(a)","children":[],"tail":"–(c), (e), (f), "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Sept. 2, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/799"},"text":"78 Stat. 799","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/19/s10/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–19, § 10(a)","children":[],"tail":" (related to 40:462), "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"May 25, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/22"},"text":"81 Stat. 22","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/448/tVI/s607"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–448, title VI, § 607","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Aug. 1, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/534"},"text":"82 Stat. 534","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/242/tV/s524/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–242, title V, § 524(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Feb. 5, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1939"},"text":"101 Stat. 1939","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “section 3324(a) and (b) of title 31” are substituted for “section 3648 of the Revised Statutes, as amended” in section 702(a) of the Housing Act of 1954 (ch. 649, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/641"},"text":"68 Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":") because of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1982-09-13/s4/b"},"text":"section 4(b) of the Act of September 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Public Law 97–258","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1067"},"text":"96 Stat. 1067","children":[],"tail":"), the first section of which enacted Title 31, United States Code. The words “municipalities and other” are omitted as being included in “public agencies”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “in any way” are omitted as unnecessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the word “rules” is omitted as being included in “regulations”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
